We officially have national finalists!!!! Congratulations to Jacob Bottom and Sarah Casper as their Environmental Systems, Agriscience Fair Research project has been selected as a national finalist by the National FFA Organization. We don't know the specifics yet on how they will interview electronically or when but we are over the moon excited for them. National finalists are selected by all states sending in their first place winner for each division. The research papers are then graded and scored and they will select up to 12 finalists for each area of the Agriscience Fair.

July 31 at 5:07 PM 路

Some exciting news! We applied for a National FFA grant through their Living to Serve program. We found out this afternoon that our grant was funded at the highest level of $3,000. Our Living to Serve grant will be used to engage our chapter members in growing produce year round for local food banks to provide them with fresh vegetables. The funds will allow us to purchase 3 more grow towers to accomplish this goal. We are looking forward to getting our service project off the ground in a couple of weeks.

Blue Valley Community Action Partnership - BVCA
June 5 at 3:17 PM 路

In the month of June we're honoring the people, businesses and organizations who have made donations to our food pantries and emergency assistance programs during the COVID-19 pandemic.
First up are 13 members of the Friend High School Class of 2020, who donated $1,000 to the Saline County Food Pantry.
The students raised the money over the course of their high school careers. While we're saddened they and all the seniors in our service area weren't able to finish their final year in the way they imagined, we're honored and humbled that these students chose to donate to our organization.
Class president William Yokel and secretary Mikayla Hausman explained why they chose BVCA, and also told us what's next for them. We wish them the very best and we're grateful for their generosity.

post_text:
As you probably have heard, Governor Ricketts announced that, beginning June 1, schools may open weight rooms. The District remains concerned about the health and safety of all students and staff members. As a result, a parent or guardian who wishes to allow his or her child to use the weight room must sign a form acknowledging the risks associated with the use of the weight room. Students must follow all social distancing and safety requirements. While the District endeavors to keep District property safe and clean, there is no guarantee that any surface, equipment or atmosphere is free from any germs, virus or other condition, and any person who voluntarily chooses to use the weight room does so at his or her own risk.
The form can be picked up at the office, emailed to you or off our website.
Email: david.kraus@friendschool.org

post_text:
New guidelines from the NSAA.

The requirement for students entering the7th grade to have a physical exam is Nebraska state education law and we do not have the ability to waive that requirement. However, the physicals that the current 7th graders have for the 2019-2020 school year can be used for NSAA purposes for the 2020-2021 school year.

After discussions with legal counsel and our insurance provider, due to our catastrophic insurance requirements, all current 8th grade students that are going to enter the 9th grade in 2020, will STILL be required to get a sports physical for the 2020-2021 school year. All other high school students entering grades 10, 11 & 12 grades that have a sports physical for 2019-2020 school year, can use that physical for the 2020-2021 school year.

post_text:
FPS juniors, along with juniors from Dorchester, Exeter-Milligan, Shickley, McCool, and Heartland, spent Tuesday, February 11, at Exeter Public School for the Blue River Cohort College & Career Fair organized by their school counselors.

Students rotated through sessions about money management, getting into college, how to cope with stress and manage wellness, as well as other topics. Students also had the chance to hear from and talk to representatives from four area businesses and learn about the skills and qualities needed to be a strong employee. Various college and business representatives were also on hand over the lunch break for students to connect with and visit.

FPS sends a special thanks to Denice Kovanda (E-M school counselor) and the Exeter-Milligan administration and staff who hosted the event again this year.

post_text: The Friend Schoolwide Geography Bee was held Wednesday, January 15th in the Media Center. Students in grades 4th  8th competed at the classroom level to advance to the schoolwide finals. The ten finalists were Jacob Behrends, Zayde Arp, Lindsay Landis, Caleb Black, Hunter Svehla, Keila Ricenbaw, Gabby Theis, Breckan Schluter, Mataya Schwisow and Harley Vajgrt. The winner of the Geography Bee was Breckan Schluter from the 8th grade. Second place went to Lindsay Landis of the 5th grade class and third place went to Caleb Black in the 6th grade. Congratulations to all our finalists. Paul Martin Geography Bee Sponsor

shared_text:
Nebraska Medicine
December 20, 2019 at 12:47 PM 路

The town of Friend, Nebraska lived up to its name today, delivering gifts for our pediatric patients. The Arp family organized the effort in honor of Beckett Arp. Beckett's organs were donated after he died in a car accident in 2015 just five days before his 7th birthday.
This year Friend Public School was joined by Exeter-Milligan Public Schools, as well as Meridian Public School, The Meridian students donated in honor of two of their students who became organ donors after a terrible car accident.
All these items are already brightening the holidays for families who will be spending Christmas in the hospital. Our thanks to the Arp family and all the schools that took part!

shared_text:
EMF FFA Chapter
November 9, 2019 at 4:25 PM 路

We are excited to announce that our chapter was selected to receive a $ 1,000 NIFA grant. Our chapter put in for this grant at the end of September and we found out yesterday that our project has been approved for funding. We will now have grow towers at both of our school locations. Chapter members will be able to grow fresh produce for the school lunch programs and we are hopefully going to be able to engage some of our elementary students in helping plant seeds for the growing system. The chapter will receive our banner on stage at State FFA Convention in April. We will be posting pictures of this project as it progresses.

FEA Scholarship for College Senior
Friend Education Association (FEA) is offering a $400 scholarship to a college student entering his/her senior year in 2019-20, and pursuing a degree in education.

Applicants must be Friend High School graduates. Interested candidates should send a letter of application and an official college transcript to Amy Wiese, Secretary of FEA at Friend Public School, PO Box 67.

Deadline to apply is Monday July 8th.

May 31, 2019 at 4:14 PM 路

Last week, members of the EMF Officer Team had the opportunity to attend COLT 5 leadership conference in Aurora. They were broken up into their particular office groups to learn their duties, and having a chance to work together as a team to make goals for themselves, the rest of the team, and for the whole chapter for the upcoming year. Also competing in competitions: the team got 3rd out of 6 teams for opening/closing ceremonies, and receiving a gold rating for the digital media (website/social media) competition. Great job to all these young leaders, and a very exciting start for whats to come next year!

post_text: Kindergarten attended their Spring Field Trip on Friday, May 3rd! We went to the Lincoln Children's Zoo where we saw penguins, bees, and much more! We then went to Antelope Park for lunch and play time. We ended the day at the Lincoln Children's Museum. We loved the new Ninja Warrior exhibit and the Hyvee Grocery Store. We had 15 students and 11 adults attend! :)

post_text: On April 13 the Friend Electric Car Team traveled to Lincoln UNL East campus to race. They completed 75 laps placing 1st. April 27th they will be heading to Hastings where they have reset and broke their own record for the last 3 years.
